---
import Base from "@/layouts/Base.astro";
import {
  BRAND_NAME,
  SITE_URL,
  PARENT_ORG,
  PARENT_ORG_URL,
  PARENT_PRIVACY_URL,
} from "@/lib/config";
import { breadcrumbListSchema } from "@/lib/schema";

const canonical = `${SITE_URL}/terms`;
const jsonLd = breadcrumbListSchema([
  { name: "Home", url: SITE_URL },
  { name: "Terms", url: canonical },
]);

const effectiveDate = "May 26, 2026";
---

<Base
  title={`Terms of Use | ${BRAND_NAME}`}
  description={`Terms governing use of ${BRAND_NAME}, the public AI humanizer benchmark operated by ${PARENT_ORG}.`}
  canonical={canonical}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>
  <article
    class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-16 px-6 text-[var(--color-text-primary)] [&_h1]:text-4xl [&_h1]:font-semibold [&_h1]:tracking-tight [&_h1]:mb-8 [&_h2]:text-2xl [&_h2]:font-semibold [&_h2]:tracking-tight [&_h2]:mt-12 [&_h2]:mb-4 [&_p]:mt-4 [&_p]:leading-relaxed [&_p]:text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] [&_ul]:mt-4 [&_ul]:space-y-2 [&_ul]:pl-6 [&_ul]:list-disc [&_ul]:text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] [&_a]:text-[var(--color-accent)] [&_a:hover]:underline [&_strong]:font-semibold [&_strong]:text-[var(--color-text-primary)]"
  >
    <h1>Terms of Use</h1>

    <p>
      <strong>Effective date:</strong>
      {effectiveDate}
    </p>

    <p>
      These terms govern your use of <strong>{BRAND_NAME}</strong> at <a
        href={SITE_URL}>humanizerbench.com</a
      > (the "Site"). The Site is operated by <a
        href={PARENT_ORG_URL}
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank">{PARENT_ORG}</a
      >. By accessing or using the Site, you agree to these terms. If you do
      not agree, do not use the Site.
    </p>

    <h2>What HumanizerBench is</h2>
    <p>
      {BRAND_NAME} is a public, auditable benchmark of commercial AI
      humanizers. Each cycle, the same prompts are run through every tested
      humanizer, each output is submitted to a fixed set of commercial AI
      detectors, and the results are scored by a published deterministic
      formula. The Site publishes the leaderboard, the underlying data, the
      scoring script, and a description of the methodology.
    </p>
    <p>
      The Site does not provide an AI humanization service. It is an
      information resource. Visiting the Site does not create any account,
      contract for services, or vendor relationship with you.
    </p>

    <h2>Operator disclosure</h2>
    <p>
      {PARENT_ORG} sells one of the humanizers ranked on the leaderboard. That
      relationship is disclosed on the homepage, the <a href="/about">About</a
      > page, and the <a href="/fairness">Fairness</a> page. {PARENT_ORG} is
      held to the same methodology, scoring, and penalty rules as every other
      tested humanizer. Editorial control of the benchmark (what is tested,
      how it is scored, what is published) is independent of {PARENT_ORG}'s
      commercial product team. No payment for placement is accepted from any
      vendor, including {PARENT_ORG}.
    </p>

    <h2>Use of the benchmark data</h2>
    <p>
      You may read, cite, quote, and reference the leaderboard and the
      published data for journalistic, academic, research, comparative, and
      commercial purposes, provided that you attribute the source to "{BRAND_NAME}"
      and link to the relevant page on the Site. You may not present the data
      in a way that materially misrepresents the methodology, the scoring, or
      a specific humanizer's results.
    </p>
    <p>
      The raw cycle bundles published under <code>/data/cycles/</code> in the
      public repository linked from the footer are intended to be downloaded
      and re-run; re-running the published scoring script against the
      published inputs is expressly permitted and encouraged.
    </p>

    <h2>Trademarks and third-party names</h2>
    <p>
      Product names, trademarks, and logos referenced on the Site belong to
      their respective owners. The use of those names on the Site is for
      factual identification of the humanizers and detectors that are tested
      and does not imply any endorsement of, affiliation with, or sponsorship
      by the named parties.
    </p>

    <h2>Newsletter</h2>
    <p>
      If you submit your email address to the Site's newsletter form, your
      email will be stored and used to send periodic updates about the
      benchmark. You can unsubscribe at any time using the link in any
      newsletter email. Email handling is described in the <a
        href={PARENT_PRIVACY_URL}
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank">{PARENT_ORG} Privacy Policy</a
      >.
    </p>

    <h2>No warranties</h2>
    <p>
      The Site, the leaderboard, the underlying data, and the scoring outputs
      are provided "as is" and "as available." {BRAND_NAME} and {PARENT_ORG}
      make no warranties, express or implied, including warranties of
      merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, accuracy, or
      non-infringement. The benchmark reflects the behavior of third-party
      humanizers and detectors at a specific point in time; those products
      change frequently, and the published results may not reflect current
      vendor behavior.
    </p>
    <p>
      The leaderboard is an informational comparison and should not be relied
      on as the sole basis for any purchasing, academic, legal, or business
      decision. Detector outputs reflect the verdicts of third-party
      commercial detectors as observed during a specific cycle and are not
      determinations of authorship, originality, or academic integrity.
    </p>

    <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
    <p>
      To the maximum extent permitted by law, {BRAND_NAME} and {PARENT_ORG},
      and their respective officers, employees, and agents, will not be
      liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
      punitive damages, or any loss of profits, revenues, data, or goodwill,
      arising out of or in connection with your use of, or inability to use,
      the Site, the leaderboard, or the published data. Aggregate liability
      for any direct damages will not exceed one hundred U.S. dollars
      (USD $100).
    </p>

    <h2>Vendor concerns and corrections</h2>
    <p>
      If you are a humanizer or detector vendor and you believe the
      methodology was misapplied to your product, contact the operator (see
      below). Submissions will be reviewed against the published methodology
      and scoring script. Corrections, if warranted, will be made
      transparently and disclosed in the next cycle. Disagreement with the
      methodology itself is not, on its own, grounds for an adjustment to
      published results.
    </p>

    <h2>Privacy</h2>
    <p>
      Information collected by the Site, including newsletter signups and
      server-side request logs, is handled in accordance with the <a
        href={PARENT_PRIVACY_URL}
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank">{PARENT_ORG} Privacy Policy</a
      >, which is incorporated into these terms by reference.
    </p>

    <h2>Acceptable use</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>
        Do not attempt to disrupt the Site, scrape it in a way that imposes
        unreasonable load, or interfere with other users.
      </li>
      <li>
        Do not submit other people's email addresses to the newsletter form.
      </li>
      <li>
        Do not misrepresent the published methodology, scoring, or
        per-humanizer results.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Changes to these terms</h2>
    <p>
      These terms may be updated from time to time. Material changes will be
      reflected in the effective date at the top of this page. Continued use
      of the Site after a change constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.
    </p>

    <h2>Governing law</h2>
    <p>
      These terms are governed by the laws applicable to {PARENT_ORG}'s
      operating jurisdiction, without regard to conflict-of-laws principles.
      The specific jurisdiction is described in the <a
        href={PARENT_PRIVACY_URL}
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank">{PARENT_ORG} Privacy Policy</a
      > and supporting policies.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about these terms, methodology disputes, and correction
      requests can be directed to the operator via <a
        href={PARENT_ORG_URL}
        rel="noopener noreferrer"
        target="_blank">{PARENT_ORG_URL}</a
      >.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
